cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the behavior of a transport protocol over a satellite communication system. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of fully encrypted QUIC on end users' quality of experience. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of a real satellite public access. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses congestion control in QUIC. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is the least likely but still possible as the paper mentions the page load time of a heavy page.
